            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>An <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0021.xml" addr="FA-0021" title="Orthonormal">orthonormal set</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U = \{x_n : n ∈ N\}]]></fr:tex> of a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000U.xml" addr="FA-000U" title="Hilbert Space">Hilbert space</fr:link> H is <fr:em>complete (note that this is <fr:strong>not</fr:strong> in the sense of a complete metric <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001C.xml" addr="FA-001C" title="Space">space</fr:link>)</fr:em>  if it satisfies <fr:em>any</fr:em> of the equivalent conditions (a)-(e) in <fr:strong>Theorem</fr:strong>:</fr:p>
            <fr:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U = \{u_n : n \in  \mathbb {N}\}]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000T.xml" addr="FA-000T" title="Orthonormal sequence">orthonormal sequence</fr:link> of a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000U.xml" addr="FA-000U" title="Hilbert Space">Hilbert space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex>, then the following conditions are equivalent:</fr:p>
            <fr:p><fr:strong>(a)</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\langle  u_n, x \rangle  = 0]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n \in  \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> implies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x = 0]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p><fr:strong>(b)</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x = \sum _{n \in  \mathbb {N}} \langle  u_n, x \rangle  u_n]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  H]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p><fr:strong>(c)</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||x||^2 = \sum _{n \in  \mathbb {N}} |\langle  u_n, x \rangle |^2]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  H]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p>(This is the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001A.xml" addr="FA-001A" title="Parseval's identity">Parseval's identity</fr:link>)</fr:p>
            <fr:p><fr:strong>(d)</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[U] = H]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p><fr:strong>(e)</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0024.xml" addr="FA-0024" title="Maximal orthonormal set">maximal</fr:link> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000T.xml" addr="FA-000T" title="Orthonormal sequence">orthonormal sequence</fr:link></fr:p>
            <fr:p>
              <fr:strong>Informally</fr:strong>
            </fr:p>
            <fr:p>For an orthonormal set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u_\alpha ]]></fr:tex> in a Hilbert space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> to be a <fr:strong>basis</fr:strong> (or complete), it means that the set is "<fr:em>large enough</fr:em>" to represent any vector in the space.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>An <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000T.xml" addr="FA-000T" title="Orthonormal sequence">orthonormal sequence</fr:link> is <fr:em>complete</fr:em> if it's <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0014.xml" addr="FA-0014" title="Closed linear span">closed linear span</fr:link> is the whole space</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
